cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.DL 

The paper deals with the task of semantic segmentation in medical images, specifically CT scans of the brain for intracranial hemorrhage (ICH) detection. This task falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) domains. The proposed technique involves using a recursive training strategy, which is a common approach in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and deep learning (cs.DL) to improve model performance with limited data. Finally, the paper focuses on a medical application, which falls under the medical imaging (cs.MED) category.
